class Solution {

    public String reverseOnlyLetters(String s) {

        // initialize left and right pointers
        int x = 0, y = s.length() - 1;

        // convert string to char array
        char[] sa = s.toCharArray();

        // loop until pointers meet
        while (x < y) {

            boolean leftIsLetter =                     // check left character
                (sa[x] >= 'A' && sa[x] <= 'Z') ||
                (sa[x] >= 'a' && sa[x] <= 'z');

            boolean rightIsLetter =                    // check right character
                (sa[y] >= 'A' && sa[y] <= 'Z') ||
                (sa[y] >= 'a' && sa[y] <= 'z');

            if (leftIsLetter && rightIsLetter) {        // if both are letters
                char temp = sa[x];                      // store left char
                sa[x] = sa[y];                          // copy right to left
                sa[y] = temp;                           // copy temp to right
                x++;                                    // move left pointer
                y--;                                    // move right pointer
            }
            else if (!rightIsLetter) {                  // if right is not a letter
                y--;                                    // move right pointer
            }
            else if (!leftIsLetter) {                   // if left is not a letter
                x++;                                    // move left pointer
            }
        }

        return new String(sa);                          // return final string
    }
}


/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

917. Reverse Only Letters

Given a string s, reverse the string according to the following rules:

All the characters that are not English letters remain in the same position.
All the English letters (lowercase or uppercase) should be reversed.
Return s after reversing it.

Example 1:

Input: s = "ab-cd"
Output: "dc-ba"
Example 2:

Input: s = "a-bC-dEf-ghIj"
Output: "j-Ih-gfE-dCba"
Example 3:

Input: s = "Test1ng-Leet=code-Q!"
Output: "Qedo1ct-eeLg=ntse-T!"
 

Constraints:

1 <= s.length <= 100
s consists of characters with ASCII values in the range [33, 122].
s does not contain '\"' or '\\'.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

